<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="1323" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1323">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 151.07/7.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at
                                    Nogales</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Nogales</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-02">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 2, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The American Consul at Mazatlan telegraphs that the Chinese colony,
                            consisting of four hundred residents, may be compelled to leave Mexico
                            and asks whether permission could be granted for temporary residence, as
                            an act of humanity, at San Francisco or San Diego.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dye.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>